<C>__{duke}
<D>__{beer!}
<A>__{a middle aged hoodlum in a t shirt booms up to the bar.}
<C>__{hoodlum}
<D>__{god damn! what day is this saturday?}
<C>__{duke}
<D>__{more like sunday.}
<C>__{hoodlum}
<D>__{hah! that's a bitch, ain't it? last night i was home in long beach and somebody said they were runnin' the mint 400 today, so i says to my old lady, "man, i'm goin'." so she gives me a lot of crap about it, so i start slappin' her around, and the next thing you know two guys i never seen before are beating me stupid.}
<C>__{voice off}
<D>__{group 4!}
<A>__{outside, another batch of motorcycles roar away kicking up more clouds of dust.}
<C>__{hoodlum}
<D>__{then they gave me ten bucks, put me on a bus, and when i woke up here i was in downtown vegas, and for a minute all i could think was, "o jesus, who's divorcing me this time?" but then i remembered, by god! i was here for the mint 400. and, man, i tell you, it's wonderful to be here. just wonderful to be here with you people.}
